Text:
Just the start to another peaceful, uneventful day.
Or so I had thought...
U-Urgh... Please help!

Casks have tumbled down in a mountainous pile. I can
hear a voice coming from within it.
Gamma...how did you get completely buried?

I-I was simply trying to do inventory of the storeroom
when I tripped...!

Um, I stepped on a small can on the floor and fell
on my rear—

Then that can knocked over some larger cans that were
lined up—

And then those cans went flying and knocked over
some even larger cans on a shelf, and then those
even larger cans fell over one after the other and
smashed through the window of the storeroom.

Then when I stepped outside to see what happened,
the barrels stacked here came down on me like an
avalanche—I'm pretty sure that's how it happened!

Normally, I would say such stupendous clumsiness
shouldn't be possible. But with Gamma, accidents
such as this are all too likely.
Ohh, why me...

Didn't you just say that you were going to move them
so this kind of accident doesn't happen?

Yes, I did everything I could to prevent it from happening,
but this was completely outside my expectations...
So, I'm sorry! I'll make a proper apology, but first—
Could you...please help me...?!

I could get out from under here on my own...but then
something else might happen!
*sigh* I suppose I have no choice.

Phew... Thank you. I was a bit scared of trying
to move these by myself.
Are you alright? No broken bones?

No, no worries in those regards! Although my rear
is a little sore.
You really are tough...

Moving all those barrels turns into quite the pre-
breakfast workout.

Well, we've got all casks back upright, so now
it's time to clean up inside as well.
I'm sorry again for all the trouble...

It's fine. I know you didn't mean for any of this
to happen.

But you are not to do the organizing yourself. Just
give directions to some subordinates. Is that clear?

Yes, but since it was my fault, I feel I should
be the one to...

No, no need for that. Simply make a plan and give
the orders.

You're a staff officer, so issuing commands is
a better use of your talents.

Understood... Now that I think about it, I did ask
Zeta to do the organizing last time.
Yes, 26 days ago.

What a great memory you have. You even remember
the exact date...!

Oh, I would think a merchant such as yourself
would need to remember at least that much, no?

Gamma blinks in confusion at the sudden mention
of her side business.

Ulp, well... You certainly know how to hit me where
it hurts.

(Truth be told, I only remembered because it just so
happens that Zeta left for a mission on the same day.)

(An extended stealth mission. That was 26 days ago.
Zeta has yet to return.)

(Zeta is exhaustively thorough, hates blowing her
cover, and never sends periodic reports.)

(I'd like to believe that failure isn't a possibility
with a professional like her.)

(But, I have admit that I'm worried. I wonder if she's
doing alright...)
Ack!
*sigh* What is it now?

The sound of mechanisms stirring to life in response
to a magic reaction erupt from inside the storehouse.
I know this distinctive noise very well.

That may be the sound of the golem starting up,
since we have it stowed in there...

I know. Didn't we have it stored like furniture
because it malfunctioned?

Yes, that is true, but...it could be that one of the
cans bumped into it, providing just the right
jolt it needed to activate.
That seems like way too much of a coincidence...
(...But it's certainly possible. Especially with Gamma.)
Oh dear...

Today is showing all signs of turning into a much
rowdier day than usual.
<RESTART COMPLETE. ENGAGING SECURITY MODE>

<UNIDENTIFIED PERSONNEL DETECTED>
<ACTIVATING SUPPRESSION MODE>

Um, uh-oh. What do we do?! Let's see, I remember
there is an emergency shutoff button somewhere...

Where was it again? Oh yes, the base of the neck,
on the back—
*sigh* Gamma, calm down.

I take a deep breath, addressing Gamma in
a gentle voice.

I need to prevent her from panicking any further so
that this disaster doesn't spread needlessly. And,
more than anything, to keep myself calm.

If I let you handle this as you are now, the storeroom
will only end up in more of a mess.
Ulp... Y-Yes, ma'am...

Leave this to me. I'll fix this quickly, and then we
can get you to breakfast.
